Edge cases for kd
================

	>>> import kd

No more than two args on command line

	>>> kd.parse_command_line(['alan','was','here'])
	Traceback (most recent call last):
	...
	ValueError: Usage: kd directory [sub-dir]

And no less than 1

	>>> kd.parse_command_line([])
	('', None)

Directories found must be real

	>>> kd.find_dir('rubbish')
	Traceback (most recent call last):
	...
	ValueError: rubbish is not a directory

	>>> import paths
	>>> a_known_directory = paths.environ.JAB

Can send a blank as the sub-dir

	>>> kd.find_dir(a_known_directory,'')
	<path '/.../.jab'>

Same effect if sub-dir is not found
	>>> kd.find_dir(a_known_directory,'this_is_not_real')
	<path '/.../.jab'>


When main() fails it prints out nothing
	>>> import sys
	>>> sys.argv = [ 'kd', 'no_such_directory' ]
	>>> kd.main()
	1

	>>> kd.want_debugging = True
	>>> kd.find_dir('/usr/local/trunk/trackers','repo')
	kd: "def find_dir('/usr/local/trunk/trackers', 'repo')"
	kd: "def try_sub_dirs(<path '/usr/local/trunk/trackers'>, 'repo')"
	<path '/usr/local/trunk/trackers/repository'>
	>>> kd.want_debugging = False

